  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Circle
    Class Circle extends Elipse as it shares the same area and perimeter methods as an Elipse.
    Cone
    Class Cone is an extension ThreeDCurves as it shares methods and features with other Three dimensional curves such as radius, height, and a circle base.
    Cube
    The Cube class extends RectangularPrism as all methods (getVolume, getSurfaceArea, getSideLength, etc.) are shared between the two.
    Cylinder
    The cylinder class extends ThreeDCurves as it shares multiple methods and variables with the parent class.
    Elipse
    The class Elipse contains all required variables and methods to compute information about itself as well as it's child-classes.
    Kite
    Class Kite extends Quadrilaterals as it shares multiple methods and variables from it's parent class.
    Parallelogram

    Polygons
